{"word":"τίνυμαι","slug":"τίνυμαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τίνυμαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> for <el>τίνομαι</el> (<a href='S:vide'>v.</a> <a href='S:τίνω'><el>τίνω</el></a> II)\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to punish, chastise</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <el>λώβην τινύμενος</el> <i>chastising</i> insolence, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to avenge oneself</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to avenge, take vengeance for</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to exact as penalty</i>, <el>δὶς τόσα</el> <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}